Sentencas: CaxBi1.7-xW0.3O3.45-0.5x (CBW) (x = 0.00, 0.05, 0.10, 0.15, 0.20, 0.30) electrolyte material were synthesized by sol-gel self-combustion method.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of solid electrolyte CaxBi1.7-xW0.3O3.45-0.5x electrolyte material by sol-gel combution method

Sentencas: The samples were characterized by thermogravimetric-differential thermogravimetric analysis(TG-DSC), X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy (SEM), porosity and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS).
Titulo: Preparation and properties of solid electrolyte CaxBi1.7-xW0.3O3.45-0.5x electrolyte material by sol-gel combution method

Sentencas: The results show the powders CaxBi1.7-xW0.3O3.45-0.5x (CBW) with fluorite crystal structure can be obtained after the precursor was calcined at 760 degrees C. When sintered at 780 degrees C for 2 h, the compact ceramic sintered with relative density higher than 97% can be obtained.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of solid electrolyte CaxBi1.7-xW0.3O3.45-0.5x electrolyte material by sol-gel combution method

Sentencas: The electrochemical studies showed thatCa(x)Bi(1.7-x)W(0.3)O(3.45-0.5x) (CBW) have high ionic conductivity after 780 degrees C sintering.
Titulo: Preparation and properties of solid electrolyte CaxBi1.7-xW0.3O3.45-0.5x electrolyte material by sol-gel combution method

Sentencas: The sample Ca0.20Bi1.50W0.3O3.35 exhibits a conductivity of 0.07978 S .
Titulo: Preparation and properties of solid electrolyte CaxBi1.7-xW0.3O3.45-0.5x electrolyte material by sol-gel combution method

Sentencas: cm(-1) at 750 degrees C, and the activation energy is 0.845 eV, which is expected to be applied to the electrolyte materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC).
Titulo: Preparation and properties of solid electrolyte CaxBi1.7-xW0.3O3.45-0.5x electrolyte material by sol-gel combution method
